error count and time. I will refine the `report_mismatch` task to handle this, incorporating the multi-bit display logic (though for 1-bit signals like `done`, the display is simple).\\n3.  **Final Status Display:** The `final` block must check `stats1.errors`. If errors > 0, display: `SIMULATION FAILED - x MISMATCHES DETECTED, FIRST AT TIME y`. Otherwise, display `SIMULATION PASSED`. This replaces the ambiguous final block in the previous TB.\\n4.  **Functionality Preservation:** The original error counting logic (`stats1.errors` and `stats1.errors_done`) and the specific verification condition (`done_ref !== ( done_ref ^ done_dut ^ done_ref )`) must be preserved.\\n\\n**Advice to Avoid Syntax Errors:**\\n*   **Type Consistency:** Ensure all declared variables and ports use consistent types (`logic`, `reg`, `wire`). The original TB had issues mixing these in assignments and definitions.\\n*   **Task/Function Body:** Tasks/functions must be properly delimited, and all statements inside them must end with a semicolon (`;`). The use of multi-line string literals (`$display("\n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n    \n   